divs: sighting detailsi was driving towards camden on route 17a on way home. i was comming home from working at nuclear plant. i observed low airborne lights to my left comming from williamstown ny heading mtowards oneida lake. i thought aircraft was going to crash as hancock field not too far away. i pulled over on side of road as i thought crash was imminent. craft eventually flew over top of truck at tree top level around 60'. moving at a very slow speed. 3 corner lights steady actinic white, 1 central light pulsating orange. outline of large 300' triangular\delta craft was very clear. graphite coloration. no sound. no effects to truck. it did not appear to pay any attention to me yet there was some fear. i wanted to get a better look at it, so went home to get 650 power telescope but craft was obscured by trees. there was another witness, but he prefers not to comment as he is still employed at nuclear facility.
Summary: Typical black triangle as shown in Belgian UFO photos.
